{"questionId":"3232798","questionHtml":"<p>Find the equation of this curve.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>equation is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math></p>\n<p>finding an expression for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo> </mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> with unknown coefficients &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo> </mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math></p>\n<p>setting up two equations using two points AND/OR one equation using the</p>\n<p>gradient function &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>three correct equations&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>9</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>36</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>9</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>11</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>444444</mn><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>66666</mn><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>(and hence <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>9</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>11</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></math>)&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"3232798","referenceCode":"23M.1.AHL.TZ1.10c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the equation of this curve.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.3—Differentiating polynomials, n E Z","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.1—Equations of straight lines, parallel and perpendicular","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.9—HL modelling functions","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.8—Use of technology to solve systems of linear equations and polynomial equations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}